reviews.review_text: GREAT! I only overflew the other copies of this show but returned to this one immediately for I found it the best sounding one! It IS a great thing, a very welcome supplement to my 1980 collection and the whole mediatheque of GD concerts, and I may recommend especially ESTIMATED and the DRUMS SPACE section. N-JOY!

I hope he has the sense to run.. Great energy to this show! FUNKY 80'..Sound quality is pretty good.
The first set is what sticks out to me with the Ramble on Rose sandwiched between a nice Lazy Lightning>Supp and Lost Sailor>Saint!! Woooo Hoooooooo..Nothing special in 2nd set..just a nice solid show from start to finish. I'm only a DEADHEAD with an opinion..BUT..Give it a whirl!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
